
			 Nimby-Doc
			 =========


Topics
------

  1. Introduction
  2. License
  3. Install
  A. Credits
  B. Bugs
  C. Resources


1. Introduction
---------------

This package is a  distribution of software documentation in
GNU Texinfo  format.  All the documents are  a conversion of
existing  documentation   in  other  formats   from  various
projects, whose code and documentation is distributed on the
Internet.


2. License
----------

All the files have a specific documentation license.


3. Install
----------

Read   the   "README.build"   file   for  details   on   the
infrastructure requirements.  Then do this:

  $ mkdir "=build"
  $ cd "=build"
  $ ./configure
  $ make
  $ make install

by default  Info, HTML  and PDF files  are build.   To build
only selected targets:

  $ make info
  $ make html
  $ make pdf


A. Credits
----------

The    conversion   to   Texinfo    is   by    Marco   Maggi
<marc.maggi-ipsu@poste.it>.   Refer to the  individual files
for the original authors.


B. Bugs
-------

Bug reports  are appreciated.  Please use  the issue tracker
at GitHub.


